track.name: All of You
comments: The cats got style I mean he can play daddy can you dig it.
Can he play the trumpet or what :-)
I'm no expert on jazz, but this song is great. I feel all warm and relaxed inside...
Only heard Miles Davis once or twice.....LOVELY! Real music.
Hmm, it's hard for me to choose between Miles Davis and Charlie Parker as the best jazz players...
The best of all jazz players, ever...and for ever!

Saw Miles in Melbourne Australia, 2 nights in a row in a smaller sized concert hall, probably about the same year, during the tour where he did "human nature" and "time after time". Wasn't quite the modal hard bop that I love so much from his mamoth work, but wow, it was amazing. Rivetting. A genius sadly missed.

I saw him live @ the Hollywood Bowl in 1985.
I will never forget that evening.
